# Market Beat — files that should NEVER be committed.
# This is now a "standalone / fire-and-forget" setup.
# Each run pulls fresh data, LLM (or agent) writes report.json,
# daily.js --strict produces the final timestamped HTML in ../uploads/.
# No history, no diff, no previous, no jsonl, no need to commit data files back.
# Only commit the *code* (js, md, schema) + the final HTML in uploads/.

# All generated data / intermediate reports (temporary per run)
report.json
report.previous.json
marketdata.json
insiders.json
insiders.block.html
marketbeat_report.html
marketbeat_report.previous.html
marketbeat_diff.html
scoreboard_*.html
diff.json
*.jsonl

# Linter & enrichment scratchpads — agent reads + discards
lint.prompt.md
enrich.prompt.md
enrich.patch.json
enrich.patch.*.json

# Legacy date-suffixed (safety)
report.[0-9]*.json
marketbeat_report_[0-9]*.html
marketbeat_diff_[0-9]*.html
diff.[0-9]*.json
